    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require companies to tell applicants the status of their job application.",
        "additional_details": "A simple reply from an employer can help better a person's options. People seeking work explore and apply for various types of employment, unskilled jobs, career and training programs or apprenticeships; and often, many of these jobs would start around the same time. Some options may be better than others depending on the individual, and a simple reply of \u201cyes\u201d, \u201cno\u201d or \u201cstill being reviewed\u201d can improve a person on making a better choice financially or for their lifestyle.\r\n\r\nPlacing an applicant in a state of suspense and stress, sometimes for months when it comes to programs and apprenticeships is a cruel situation to place anyone in, when a feedback about the application will allow an applicant to move on and accept other options.",
        "background": "Applicants should have a right to receive a reply from employers. This petition isn\u2019t to push for critical feedback, but a simple \u201cyes, you have a job\u201d or \u201cno, you haven\u2019t.\" Failure to reply within a reasonable time-frame should be punished by fines, depending on the company's size.",
